\chapter{Rigidity over a base field $k$: morphisms from a genus-$0$ curve to a group scheme are constant}
\label{chap:RigidityKbar}

This chapter introduces the project's named declaration for the M2.a sub-step of the genus-$0$ Albanese-witness argument: rigidity of morphisms from a smooth proper geometrically irreducible curve of genus $0$ to a smooth proper geometrically irreducible group scheme, \textbf{over an arbitrary base field $k$} (no algebraic closure assumed; see \S "Iter-127 over-k commitment" below). The classical statement (Mumford, \emph{Abelian Varieties}, Chapter~II~\S4) is

\begin{quote}
  \emph{Let $A$ be an abelian variety of positive dimension over an algebraically closed field $\bar k$. Then every morphism $f \colon \mathbb P^1_{\bar k} \to A$ is constant.}
\end{quote}

This is the keystone classical input for the C.2.d sub-step of Jacobian.tex \S C.2: the genus-$0$ universal-property step of $\thm{thm:nonempty_jacobianWitness}$ that concludes the universal-pointed-morphism factorisation by ruling out positive-dimensional images of $f \colon C \to A$ when $C$ has genus $0$ and a $k$-rational marked point.

The full proof of the keystone is gated on a Mathlib pile (cotangent-triviality of a group scheme + scheme-level $\mathrm d f = 0 \Rightarrow$ $f$ factors through $\Spec k$ + characteristic-$p$ absolute-Frobenius iteration); see \cref{sec:RigidityKbar_shared_pile} for the inventory. The iter-126 scaffolding lands the named declaration with a single \texttt{sorry} body whose residual is exactly the keystone above; the body is closed iter-128+ as the shared pile lands.

\paragraph{Iter-127 over-k commitment.} Prior strategy iterations routed through base-change to the algebraic closure $\bar k$ followed by Galois descent of morphism equality (M2.c in STRATEGY.md, $\sim 4$--$8$ iter / $300$--$500$ LOC). The iter-127 over-k analogist (\texttt{analogies/cotangent-vanishing-pile-over-k.md}) verified that all three active pieces of the shared cotangent-vanishing pile build directly over an arbitrary base field $k$: piece (i) cotangent triviality uses the intrinsic shear iso $(a, b) \mapsto (a, a \cdot b)$ (scheme map over any base); piece (ii) \texttt{Differential.ContainConstants} is $k$-agnostic in Mathlib; piece (iii) uses absolute Frobenius $F_X$ (intrinsic to $X$, no perfectness/alg-closure required). The Galois-descent step M2.c and its companion \texttt{geomIrred.exists\_kalg\_pt} (M2.c.aux) are DROPPED, saving 7--13 iter / 500--900 LOC. \textbf{The Lean declaration's signature is already $k$-agnostic} (\texttt{[Field kbar]}, no \texttt{[IsAlgClosed kbar]}); only docstrings, the variable name \texttt{kbar} (a legacy from the iter-126 over-$\bar k$ framing; rename to \texttt{k} is a low-priority cleanup refactor scheduled for iter-128+), and this chapter's prose framing shift to the over-k reading.

